                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hicks</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1893</hi>
                        </date>. (Received April 9.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Hicks reports that he has received a reply to a note that he had addressed to
                    the Peruvian government before sending his telegram of the 5th to the Department
                    and in which he had asked for information and called attention to the grave
                    nature of the incident; that reply expresses regret, promises that reparation
                    will be made for damage sustained and the guilty parties at Mollendo punished,
                    and announces the removal of the subprefect in charge. He suggests that in view
                    of equity displayed in the reply protest should not be made unless so directed
                    by the Department.</p>
            </div>
